The paper deals with the problem of automatically selecting an appropriate model for a given dataset, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a method for selecting from a large space of matrix decomposition models using a context-free grammar and a small toolbox of reusable algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
